data.description: Engineering principles of unsaturated soils as they apply to geotechnical and geoenvironmental systems. Effect of soil water suction and stress on hydraulic conductivity, shear strength, and compressibility of soils in the context of geoengineering problems of flow and stability. Knowledge of Soil Mechanics [such asCIV ENGR/​G L E  330] is required.
data.title: UNSATURATED SOIL GEOENGINEERING
